        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 3 at 2:44PM CDT by NWS Jackson MS</headline>
        <description>At 244 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Mound, or 7 miles southeast of Tallulah, moving southeast at 15 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

This strong thunderstorm will be near...
Mound and Afton around 250 PM CDT.
Vicksburg and Le Tourneau around 305 PM CDT.
Yokena around 310 PM CDT.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
